      "writtenOn": "2019-05-06T21:35:40Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I tried this.\nI\u0027d have to pass the SkRecorder along with the work item. In other words, I need to capture it. But it\u0027s a unique_ptr, I\u0027d have to move it into the lambda. Since c++14 there is supposed to be a way to do this\n\nstd::unique_ptr\u003cSkRecorder\u003e recorder\n[c \u003d std::move(recorder)](){ use c}\n\nbut I haven\u0027t gotten it to compile, something is trying to copy the unique_ptr somewhere. It looks like std::function is always copied.",
      "parentUuid": "398a3b4c_7ec5a3d0",
